# Notes on Anki

###### Video Information:
**Title:** [How To Use Anki Like A Pro](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WmPx333n5UQ)
**Duration:** 21:23
**By:** [TheMDJourney](https://www.youtube.com/@TheMDJourney)

### What is Anki?
- Anki is an intelligent flashcard system designed around space recognition
- Alternates: Quizlet
- Anki recognizes which topics you are good/bad at
	- Anki then shows you more flashcards which you are bad at to improve your weaknesses
- Free

### Setup Anki
- [Download](https://apps.ankiweb.net/)
- [Register for account]() and login 
- Get various addons
##### Decks
- Name the deck based on the subject
	- Under it, make a new deck for each topic/"lecture"
#### Flashcards
- Once the deck is created, click on it. 
- Click add
- It will open a popup with options for flashcards. 
- Click Type: X to change the type ![Pasted image 20221210105140.png](data:image/png;base64,)
- **Basic Flashcard**:
	- Simple front and back with a question and answer.  
	- Then, the trial deck would show a singular flashcard to review
- **Basic and Reverse Flashcard:**
	- Good for language translation
	- Memorizing structure
	- What it does is that it shows you two cards in the study session, one with the question posed as answer, and then vice-versa. 
	- Sample use case:
		- Q: Estados Unidos
		- A: United States
		- Then Q&A are reversed
- **Cloze Flashcard**
	- It is useful if you want to block off a specific phrase in a definition, to practise terminology or an equation
		- Use \[...] button or Ctrl+Shift+C
	- Multiple flashcards can be made from one question
		- c1 and c2 would indicate two flashcards
		- c1 and c1 would mean two guesses in one
- **Image Occlusion**
	- Install add-on ([link](https://ankiweb.net/shared/info/1374772155)) (code: 1374772155)
	- Choose flashcard type as image occlusion
	- Can be used to block off different parts of an image
	- E.g. if labelling parts of heart, click over the structures that need to be known 
	-  Add card options are hide one guess one and hide all guess one. The number of covered labels create those many flashcards
- You can use flashcards from the internet. File -> Import

## Strategies to Increase Retention
- Use screenshot tool and copypaste into front-back to save time. Increases the process of creating flashcards. can create a folder of them
- Can use tag function to label a card. Can add tags based on difficulty level. Then, browse (B) based on tags with a filtered deck. `Search; tag: "tagname"`
- Create a mental timer for each flashcard, if you cant get it just click again
- Breakdown flashcard information
